==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈʃɻɪŋk/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪŋk}}

===Etymology===
Cognate with Dutch {{term|schrinken||to shrink|lang=nl}}.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|shrinks|shrinking|'''[[shrank]]''' or '''[[shrunk]]'''|'''[[shrunk]]''' or '''[[shrunken]]'''}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To cause to become [[smaller]].
#: ''The dryer '''shrank''' my sweater.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To become smaller.
#: ''This garment will '''shrink''' when wet.''
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To [[cower]] or [[flinch]].
#: ''Molly '''shrank''' away from the blows of the whip.''
# {{context|intransitive|figuratively|lang=en}} To attempt to avoid an unwanted or intimidating [[duty]]
#: ''To '''shrink''' from a task.''

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|avoid an unwanted task}} [[funk]], [[shirk]]

====Antonyms====
* {{sense|to cause to become smaller}}  [[expand]], [[grow]], [[enlarge]], [[stretch]]
* {{sense|become smaller}} [[expand]], [[grow]], [[enlarge]], [[stretch]]

